SIMPLE: offer
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Offer
<hw>Of"fer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Offered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Offering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>offren</ets>,
<er>AS</er>. <ets>offrian</ets> to sacrifice, fr. L. <ets>offerre</ets>;
<ets>ob</ets> (see <er>OB-</er>) + <ets>ferre</ets> to bear, bring. The
English word was influenced by F. <ets>offrir</ets> to offer, of the
same origin. See 1st <er>Bear</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To present,
as an act of worship; to immolate; to sacrifice; to present in prayer or
devotion; -- often with <xex>up</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou shalt <qex>offer</qex> every day a bullock for a sin offering
for atonement.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xxix. 36.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A holy priesthood to <qex>offer</qex> up spiritual sacrifices.</q>
<rj><qau>1 Pet. ii. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bring to or before; to hold out to; to present
for acceptance or rejection; <as>as, to <ex>offer</ex> a present, or a
bribe; to <ex>offer</ex> one's self in marriage.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>offer</qex> thee three things.</q> <rj><qau>2 Sam. xxiv.
12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To present in words; to proffer; to make a proposal
of; to suggest; <as>as, to <ex>offer</ex> an opinion</as>. With the
infinitive as an objective: To make an offer; to declare one's
willingness; <as>as, he <ex>offered</ex> to help me</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To attempt; to undertake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All that <qex>offer</qex> to defend him.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To bid, as a price, reward, or wages; <as>as, to
<ex>offer</ex> a guinea for a ring; to <ex>offer</ex> a salary or
reward.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To put in opposition to; to manifest in an offensive
way; to threaten; <as>as, to <ex>offer</ex> violence, attack,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To propose; propound; move; proffer; tender;
sacrifice; immolate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Offer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Offer
<hw>Of"fer</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To present itself; to
be at hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The occasion <qex>offers</qex>, and the youth complies.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make an attempt; to make an essay or a trial; --
used with <xex>at</xex>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Without <xex>offering</xex> at any
other remedy.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He would be <qex>offering</qex> at the shepherd's voice.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will not <qex>offer</qex> at that I can not master.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Offer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Offer
<hw>Of"fer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>offre</ets>, fr. <ets>offrir</ets> to offer, fr. L.
<ets>offerre</ets>. See <er>Offer</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of offering, bringing forward, proposing, or
bidding; a proffer; a first advance.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧This <xex>offer</xex>
comes from mercy.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is offered or brought forward; a proposal
to be accepted or rejected; a sum offered; a bid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When <qex>offers</qex> are disdained, and love denied.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Attempt; endeavor; essay; <as>as, he made an
<ex>offer</ex> to catch the ball</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Some
<xex>offer</xex> and attempt.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Offerable</ent>⟦br⟧
